history.text: I thought the cast was great!
Gal Gadot was just incredible! And I normally love Chris Pine in anything.

I agree. Gal Gadot and Chris Pine had 
AMAZING chemistry
Haven't seen any of Patty Jenkins previous films, but I would be interested after seeing this.
That was really important that they have good chemistry. The whole movie pivoted around Steve drawing Diana out into man's world and guiding her through it.
Yes her direction was just wonderful. It was so intensely empowering to see her use love and peace so formidably and through a female super hero finally.
She did seem like the perfect director to take on a strong female super hero film.
I haven't seen her previous films, but I'm definitely on board after this piece.
Great to finally see a DC film score big with critics and fans.
I also thought the action scenes were top notch.
And finally a female superhero lead. Marvel hasn't given us that yet.
Let's hope DC continues the trend! Great seeing something different for once.
Amazing too how they managed to include all these Greek myth elements without getting too cheesy.

I was surprised
 they kept it to mostly just montages of the Amazon mythology
Plus using the entire island of Themyscira. The whole background somehow didn't seem ridiculous, even though it should have.
Yes, I thought the Amazon tribe was very interesting. Good use of cgi
It was super empowering to see all these woman in such a thriving and powerful society. Robin Wright was wildly inspiring.
I was worried after Batman vs. Superman, but this movie proved me wrong with it's strong cast and storytelling
I was worried too. I really enjoyed setting it in WWI, and keeping it from being too gritty.
The great score helped a lot as well
Good pacing also, didn't feel like it dragged
The two villains on top of the natural progression of World War I kept it really fresh. General Erich Ludendorff going rogue made it just a storm of problems to address. It was intense.
I agree, intense is a good word. Especially the battles.
The battles were incredible. I was shocked over how on the edge of my seat I was for the German beach invasion of Themyscira
The special effects really mad them even more memorable. I liked the mix of practical and cgi.
The special effects in the fight between Ares and DIana were incredible in the final fight.
Oh yes, the climactic showdown between Wonder Woman and Ares was great!

I 
was really upset when Steve sacrificed himself. I really wanted them to continue, because I enjoyed their dynamic so much!
I can totally understand that haha
I loved the character before the movie, so really the whole thing was just a wonderful ride for me.
Agreed. Nice chat. Goodbye!
Thanks! It was nice!
